		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Doug Crandell</span></strong> grew up on a hog farm and has worked in a ceiling-tile factory, an auto shop, a mop factory, and a steel mill. His first novel, <em>Man vs. Nature</em> (portions of which appeared in the <em>Indiana Review</em>, <em>Nebraska Review</em>, and <em>Night Train</em>), is scheduled to be published in 2004 by Ludlow Press, a new Lower East Side publishing house. He lives in Smyrna, Georgia.</p><a href="/contributors/doug-crandell" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
